annotation.TEXT: BTW, back here is where I originally got the P-switch from.
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and I've decided to do a video playthrough of this particular VLDC 8 level!

Can't do much above the water here, so let's put on our Iron Boots and sink to the bottom... Wait, Mario doesn't need Iron Boots, and he can hold his breath indefinitely in 2D games, so the Zora Tunic isn't needed either. He still has to watch out for fish, though.

...you can end up on the roof, and continuing to the left would let you return to the first part of the level, where the water level was at its highest. (Yep, we're not actually changing the water level, but instead heading to nearly identical rooms with different water levels.)
Push!
Ow, that's me being dumb.
That Cheepo is kinda hard to burn without hitting my head on the spikes, so I'll let it live.
I don't think there's anything in this room that requires a P-switch besides getting past that one wall, but if there is, let me know.
However, all of the enemies in that vertical shaft respawned, which makes the Yoshi coin kind of a hassle to reach, so I'm not gonna bother. (I've got a different Yoshi-coin-related plan...)
Okay, let's put this P-switch to use. Carry it back here and activate it to reveal ? blocks and a door.
That's kinda interesting how this area works. The other two entrances to this sublevel must've been set to make this area an underwater level, but this entrance next to the goal sphere wasn't.
Doesn't look like there's anything special in the alcoves up there.
That's me still being dumb, but whatever. This battle is done, and this hack strips me of my power ups when I return to the overworld anyway.
Well, I don't know if there's an actual moon in Waterflow Temple, but this one will do. (However, if there is a moon in Waterflow Temple, let me know.)
Now, in Night of Fire, this message box normally tells you about the P-switch, but since I entered this level through Waterflow Temple, and Waterflow Temple has no messages, this one is blank.
Oh, hello. There's a hidden 1-up here. Also, you can climb up to the door above, but you can't enter it this time.
Watch out for falling flames while climbing this vine. Try to climb it quickly, and favor its left side.
Oh, man! Fish saws! But, they're just as dangeous as regular saws, so don't take this silly sprite lightly!
Okay, so over there is the door that leads to the end of the level, but I can't reach it from here.
Whoa, I hope I don't accidentally get myself crush-killed or something.
Now, this block is where you'd normally get a cape, so I'll stay caped this time.
I love doing that.
Huh, there's this one ledge tile right here in the middle of nowhere, but I can't stand on it, nor can I place the P-switch on it.
Instead, I think I'll just slip under the bottom of the level here. (Going under the level to the left doesn't lead anywhere meaningful.)
Let's head down this way again.
Well, I'm not going to actually go back there, so let's return to where I was and try shell jumping to the right.
Okay, the screen stops scrolling to the right here, so this is the end of this minus world.
There's nothing but a bottomless pit over to the right, so let's go back to the left.
Take the lower route here so that you can get a Yoshi coin. Just be careful of the single-block landings.
The coins in the floor and ceiling here indicate a few safe spots.
Well, I hope you all enjoying watching me play through Waterflow Temple and Night of Fire! See y'all later!
Why is there a sorta glitchy piece of the level over here?
Push!
Toasty!
So, let's head over here. Watch out for the spiky ceiling.
And thus, Waterflow Temple is now considered 100% complete! But... let's go back in time and do something different...
Do a sprinting jump here.
However, I don't want to go that way.

Okay, that door is obviously one-way. Also, there's Yoshi coin #5, but it's rather tricky to reach, and requires a P-switch, which we'll find later. Now, these Bullet Bills I think are actually footballs, so you can stomp them and burninate them.
Now, the bottom door is enterable. Also, there's midpoint and a power up block that you can open with a shell to the left.
BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN! TRI-FORMATION! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! BURN TO THE GROUND!
Too bad my fireballs don't bounce off of the ledge that acts like dirt tile 1F0.
...for boss time!
By going through that pipe twice with this P-switch, I've made an extra one spawn, so I can use one of them to help me swim faster horizontally.
Hmm...? Am I on the outside of the Waterflow Temple now?
What's with this strip of dirt sticking out to the right of this structure, anyway?
I'm guessing the loose coins here were inserted as Map16 objects, since they reappeared. Either that, or this room's item memory index is set to "Index 3 No Track".
Use the opening in the floor to dodge this fish saw.
BGM: VLDC 7 - REMIX - Fire
Oh, man. I'm seriously getting an Ocarina of Time vibe from this place already. However, don't worry. This level isn't nearly as complicated as THAT dungeon.
Push!
You can slide-kill the flames, BTW.
Push!
Alright, let's head back.
Take the low road here with the help of the cape, and you can reach...
That door to the right, on the other hand, can't be entered, since there's no ledge under it.
Wow, I'm surprised I didn't get hit there. Also, there's line-guided Piranha Plants. They're the same as line-guided Fuzzies, so you can't burninate them.
BGM: CUSTOM - Hydrothermal Hollow, by Lui37
Push!
This way, you can land here, where you'll find a Koopa.
That door there is where I'm supposed to head next, but I'm not going into it quite yet.
Push!
Awesome, I managed to get it without getting any part of myself cutoff in such a way that wouldn't be accepted at SMW Central!
Whoa, this is weird...
Oh, hey. I burned that difficult-to-burn-without-hitting-your-head-on-the-spikes fish there. I think it's easier to burn if you're not carrying a P-switch.
This room auto-scrolls, so use caution.
Well, who knows why the screen exit for that door was set to here, but I guess I'll play through this level now. Fortunately, this level isn't that long.
...a MOOOONNN!!!
Hit some hidden blocks at the beginning of this room and you can quickly reach this P-switch, which'll become important later.
I don't know why I let the second Cheepo down there live, though. Maybe I was just feeling generous or something.
There's the P-switch, and yes, this pipe is two-way, so it's obvious how to reach Yoshi coin #5 now.
Once at the bottom here, if you look to the right, you'll see the goal sphere. I'm not too far away from actually reaching it.

Nuts, not high enough. Maybe I could've tried wall jumping, but I'm not going to bother. Now, I thought I read somewhere that there was a moon around here, but I have no idea where. If anyone knows, let me know!
...Okaaay, I've somehow ended up in Proto Man's level, Night of Fire, which ranked 81st, and is located in the Worst World.

That's Yoshi coin #4, and those Spinies there are actually Diggin' Chuck's rocks, just like the flames from the auto-scrolling room, so you can't roast them. Also, there's a hidden pop-up 1-up just above the single spike on the right.
Don't loiter around here, because the auto-scroll doesn't stop, and will kill you if you don't enter this door in time. (I hate when auto-scrolling rooms don't stop scrolling at the end of the room.)
Wow, I'm really surprised I didn't hit any of them!
Alright, let's see what's on the other side of that door that I can enter.
Sweet, a cape! Normally, though, you wouldn't already be powered up upon hitting that block, so I'll just switch to my flower so that I can pretend I haven't gotten a cape yet.

Also, I burned the other fish that I ignored last time. I guess I wasn't feeling so generous this time... But then again, I left a Bullet Bill alive, and I think I left a few of the earlier fish alive as well.
Do I want to go for this tricky 1-up? ...Sure, why not?
Alright, so that's another way to get Waterflow Temple marked as cleared, but let's go back in time again...
There's multiple doors down here, but I can't enter them.
Hold left and a run button as you go through this pipe.
Going this way lets you avoid a flame and get a power up. In addition, the Bouncing Chuck can't ambush you.
Oh, by the way, this door over here that I entered this room from can't be reentered. So, the only enterable door is the one just to the right.
Alright, back here at the blank message box, instead of carrying the P-switch to the left, let's just hit it here.
Once you land in the water, stay down here and take the lower route up ahead.
This pipe leads to this door, which we saw before. (Hey, that rhymes! ...Hey guys, "door" and "before" are considered rhyming words, right?)
Screen stops scrolling to the right here, so let's go into the door...
These ledges that I'm passing through are like dirt tile 1F0, which Mario can't stand on, but other sprites can hover on. This is pretty clever usage of that tile.
And, there we go! I've collected a total of 8 Yoshi coins in one level visit!
This is really weird. Also, I actually can enter that door, and I'll show you what's on the other side of it in a moment.
Okay, I've gone all the way back to when I first got to this P-switch in Waterflow Temple. This time, let's do things the intended way, starting with Yoshi coin #5.
There doesn't seem to be much else up here, though. However, by doing a shell jump to the left... (I used a couple rewinds to help me make this shell jump, BTW.)
BGM: VLDC 8 - REMIX - Boss
Hi, Yoshi!
That flame is actually Diggin' Chuck's rock. Apparently, they're digging up purple flames today.
You can also jump up to the top level, but there doesn't seem to be anything of interest there.
Ah, here's a door that I can enter.

Okay, so it appears that we're back in the main room again, but with the water level lowered. (Huh, I don't remember playing the ocarina to change the water level.) Head all the way to the left for a Yoshi coin.
That's a lot of Boos. Anyway, it's your standard Big Boo Boss. Just pelt him with three ice blocks like usual.
DOUBLE KILL!
Okay, this pipe eventually leads to that goal sphere that I showed you earlier.
Carefully navigate your way through the enemies as you ascend with the P-switch here. If you can fry the flammable/inflammable ones, and/or stomp the stompable ones, that can help.
Ah, and there's that goal sphere. Umm... What's with the flopping fish up there on the left? ...Oh, it's because this area isn't considered an underwater level when I entered it this way.
And there we go. Yoshi coin #5 is mine! Now to fall straight back down without any regard for the remaining enemies.
Alright, let's do the rest of this level normally.
So, what is this place? Some sort of minus world or something?
Falling isn't fatal here, but you will want to jump across these ? blocks to reach a Yoshi coin before falling.
I don't think I can make this platform sink any lower than that.
So, yeah. This is the reason I didn't bother with that tricky fifth Yoshi coin in Waterflow Temple. If I had gone through the trouble of getting it, there would've been no Yoshi coins here!
Ooh, wings! Here we go!
